com.nokia.maps.map

Interface MapStandardMarker

  • All Superinterfaces:
    MapObject

    public interface MapStandardMarker
extends MapObject
    This interface defines a MapObject which uses a predefined shape for its display.

    The anchor point is the offset (from the top left-hand corner) of the pixel defining the focal point of the MapStandardMarker i.e. the point on the marker's icon that the eye is drawn to.

    Size is the maximum drawing size in pixels that marker takes.

    Markers have special handling for stack order. Markers are placed over the top of any other map object types. Markers are first z-ordered by their current y axis position (markers at the bottom of the screen cover markers more at the top of the screen. Markers are only sorted by z-Index when they have the same y position.


    See Also:
    MapDisplay, MapContainer

      • setAnchor

        void setAnchor(Point anchor)
        This method sets the anchor point of the marker object. The correct anchor point varies from image to image, and depends upon the part of the image that the eye is drawn to. e.g. The hole in the centre of a doughnut or the "pointer" of a marker.
        Parameters:
        anchor - An object containing the x and y pixels of the marker's anchor point relative to the top left-hand corner of the image.

      • getAnchor

        Point getAnchor()
        This method retrieves the marker's anchor point. This should be the pixel on the the marker's image that the eye is drawn to.
        Returns:
        An object containing the x and y pixel offset of the marker's anchor point relative to the top left-hand corner of the image.
